Police say the group overpowered and tied up the security guard gaining access to the premises. JOHANNESBURG Police have shot and killed a man who was allegedly trying to steal brand new Ford vehicles with five other accomplices at Greenstone Mall in the early hours of this morning.Police say the group overpowered and tied up the security guard gaining access to the premises.The suspects then used a grinder to open the safe taking keys for three brand new cars parked outside.The police s Kay Makhubele says a shootout ensued as the group was making its way out of the car dealership with the stolen vehicles. On their way out they met the police and the security, shooting ensued and one suspect was shot and killed, four were arrested. The other suspect flee. We re investigating a case of robbery. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)